<br>
I've noticed that sometimes I levitate at the same height all the time, sometimes I slowly glide down to the ground and sometimes the glide is quiet rapid.<br>
<br>
Has anyone else noticed this?<br>
<br>
I thought at first that maybe there was some intentional design, that certain zones had stronger gravitational forces than others meaning you would float down faster. But just recently I have noticed varying rates of decent in PoK.<br>
<br>
Is this some intended element of the games design? Or is it some sort of side-effect?<br>
<br>
Just out of curiosity whats the highest anyone has ever levitated? You can get quite a view if you step of the bridge between ICO and EW and levitate around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=topums4thtry>topums 4thtry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 7:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gravity effects</span><hr size=1> your angle of sight can effect descent rates . <br>
